The paper proposes a new low-rank tensor model for video completion, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of FFT for efficient computation, which suggests a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the nuclear norm, which is a common tool in machine learning and optimization, suggesting a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of block circulant matricization, which is a technique in signal processing, suggesting a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the ability of the proposed model to reconstruct panning videos, which is a specific problem in video processing, suggesting a connection to cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing).
